Library Link Manager
Description

The following table shows all the disabled or edited library links in the model. 

To push the changes from link to library, select the appropriate block(s) and click 'Push'. To revert the changes and restore the library block, select the appropriate block(s) and click 'Restore'.

When you select a block, all other blocks below in the hierarchy are selected. The 'Push' and 'Restore' operations resolve the library link in hierarchy mode. For more information, click 'Help'.

The following table shows all the linked blocks with parameterized links. 

Parameterized links are created when any parameter(s) changes inside the linked block. 

Click 'Restore' to discard the changes in the parameter value and synchronize the value from the corresponding library block. Click 'Push' to update the corresponding library block with the changed parameter value.
